subsection.p:
A small box near (x,y,z) has mass approximately \delta(x,y,z)\,\Delta V. Adding all those small masses gives M=\iiint_E \delta(x,y,z)\,dV. For this block,
M \amp= \int_0^4\int_0^3\int_0^2 (2+z)\,dz\,dy\,dx \amp= \int_0^4\int_0^3 \left[2z+\frac{z^2}{2}\right]_0^2 \,dy\,dx \amp= \int_0^4\int_0^3 6\,dy\,dx \amp= 72.
So the total mass is \boxed{ M=72. }

